Canada Zero, a sole purpose companyincorporated in the Cayman Islands, is issuing a zero couponeurobond with a total redemption amount of 150 mln Canadiandlrs, lead manager CIBC Ltd said.    The issue matures on May 1, 2001 and is priced at 30 pct.It is secured with Canadian government bonds. The sellingconcession is 3/4 while management and underwriting each pay1/4 pct. The payment date is April 30. Listing is inLuxembourg.    A CIBC spokesmn said the issue yields 49 basis points overequivalent Canadian Treasury bonds. It is available indenominations of 5,000 and 100,000 Canadian dlrs. REUTER&#3;